data.title: Freshman Honor Roll Distinction
data.meta_site_name: Freshman Honor Roll Distinction - Division of Student Success - The University of Texas at Arlington
data.text:
First-Year Academic Excellence

First-time, first-year students with less than 30 credit hours with high academic standing are recognized each semester. They also receive special recognition from the Associate Vice Provost.

Freshman Distinction Roll

4.0 term GPA

Less than 30 semester credit hours earned at UT Arlington

At least 12 semester credit hours earned in the current term, not including pass/fail work

Freshman Honor Roll

3.5-3.99 term GPA

Less than 30 semester credit hours earned at UT Arlington

At least 12 semester credit hours earned in the current term, not including pass/fail work

Freshman Recognition (3.0-3.49 term GPA)
